@startuml c4-jotp-07g-sequence-distributed-failover
title JOTP - Distributed Failover Sequence Diagram

participant "Node A\n(Primary)" as NodeA #lightblue
participant "Node B\n(Secondary)" as NodeB #lightgreen
participant "NodeDiscovery" as Discovery
participant "FailoverController" as Failover
participant "GlobalProcRegistry" as Registry
participant "RocksDBGlobalRegistryBackend" as Backend
participant "Replicated Log\n(Future)" as ReplicatedLog #gray

== Normal Operation ==

NodeA ->> Registry: registerGlobal("order-svc", ref, "NodeA")
activate Registry
Registry ->> Backend: storeAtomic("order-svc", GlobalProcRef)
activate Backend

Backend ->> Backend: WriteBatch {registry, ack}
Backend -->> Registry: Ok
deactivate Backend

Registry -->> NodeA: registered
deactivate Registry

NodeA ->> Discovery: sendHeartbeat()
activate Discovery
Discovery ->> Discovery: updateHeartbeat("NodeA", now)
deactivate Discovery

== Node Failure Detection ==

note over Discovery
  Health check runs every 5s
  Timeout: 10s -> DEGRADED
  Timeout: 30s -> DOWN
end note

Discovery ->> Discovery: runHealthChecks()
Discovery ->> Discovery: now - lastHeartbeat > 30s

Discovery ->> Discovery: onNodeDown("NodeA")
activate Discovery

Discovery ->> Failover: trigger failover for NodeA
deactivate Discovery

== Failover Execution ==

activate Failover

Failover ->> Registry: listGlobal()
activate Registry
Registry ->> Backend: listAll()
Backend -->> Registry: Map of all registrations
deactivate Registry

note over Failover
  Find processes on NodeA:
  filter: ref.nodeName == "NodeA"
end note

Failover ->> Discovery: getHealthyNodes()
Discovery -->> Failover: ["NodeB", "NodeC"]

loop For each process on NodeA (parallel via StructuredTaskScope)
    Failover ->> Failover: select target (round-robin)
    note over Failover
      Target: NodeB
      Process: "order-svc"
    end note

    Failover ->> Registry: transferGlobal("order-svc", "NodeB")
    activate Registry

    Registry ->> Backend: compareAndSwap(name, expected, newRef)
    activate Backend

    note over Backend
      Atomic update with
      incremented sequence number
    end note

    Backend ->> Backend: WriteBatch {registry, ack}
    Backend -->> Registry: true (success)
    deactivate Backend

    Registry -->> Failover: transferred
    deactivate Registry
end

deactivate Failover

== State Recovery on Target Node ==

NodeB ->> NodeB: receive migration request
activate NodeB

NodeB ->> ReplicatedLog: replayEvents("order-svc", from=lastAckSeq)
activate ReplicatedLog
note over ReplicatedLog #gray
  Future: replicated log provides
  cross-node state durability
end note
ReplicatedLog -->> NodeB: events[]
deactivate ReplicatedLog

NodeB ->> NodeB: rebuildState(initialState, events)

NodeB ->> Registry: rehydrate("order-svc", localRef)
activate Registry
Registry ->> Backend: rehydrate(name, ref)
Backend -->> Registry: updated GlobalProcRef
deactivate Registry

NodeB ->> NodeB: start process with recovered state

note over NodeB
  Process continues transparently
  Clients see no interruption
  Location-transparent messaging
end note

deactivate NodeB

@enduml
